def create_dataframe(folder):
  folder_path= '/content/plant-seedlings-classification/train/'+ folder
  image_path=folder_path + "/*.png"
  img_df = pd.DataFrame()
  
  if os.path.isdir(folder_path): 
    fnames = pd.Series(os.listdir(folder_path))
    files1 = glob.glob(image_path)
   
    dfs1 = []
    for fp in files1:
        image1 = cv2.imread(fp,1)
        dfs1.append(cv2.imread(fp,1))
    
    image_data = pd.Series(dfs1)   
    
    img_df = img_df.assign(filename = fnames)
    img_df = img_df.assign(image = dfs1)
    img_df = img_df.assign(species=folder)
   
   
  return img_df

def display_n_images(num_images):

  from random import randint
  plt.figure(figsize=(12,12)) # plot 25 images
  for i in range(num_images):
      value = randint(0,4752)
      img=img_final.iloc[value]['image']
      plt.subplot(5,5,i+1)
      plt.xticks([])
      plt.yticks([])
      plt.grid(False)
      plt.imshow(img,cmap=plt.cm.binary)

#Initialize model
cnn = tf.keras.models.Sequential()

#Adding first convolutional layer
cnn.add(tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(32, #Number of filters 
                               kernel_size=(3,3), #Size of the filter
                               activation='relu',
                               input_shape=(150,150,3)))

#Add MaxPooling layer 1
cnn.add(tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)))

#Adding second convolutional layer
cnn.add(tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(32, #Number of filters 
                               kernel_size=(3,3), #Size of the filter
                               activation='relu', padding='same'))

#Add MaxPooling layer 2
cnn.add(tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)))

#Add dropout layer
cnn.add(tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.25))

#Flatten the output
cnn.add(tf.keras.layers.Flatten())

#Dense layer 1
cnn.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(256, activation='relu'))

#Add another dropout layer
cnn.add(tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.25))

#Dense layer 2
cnn.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='relu'))

#Add another dropout layer
cnn.add(tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.25))

#Dense layer 3
cnn.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='relu')) #, kernel_regularizer = tf.keras.regularizers.l2( l=0.01)

#Add anoter dropout layer
cnn.add(tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.25))

#Output layer
cnn.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(12, activation='softmax'))

# Compile model
#adam_opt = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(lr=0.00001)
cnn.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.RMSprop(lr=2e-4), 
              loss='categorical_crossentropy', 
              metrics=['accuracy'])

early_stopping = tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(monitor='val_acc', patience=5,verbose=1, mode='auto')
callback_list = [early_stopping]

# Initialize Sequential model
ann = tf.keras.models.Sequential()

# Input layer 
ann.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu', input_shape=(224,224,3)))

# Normalize the data
ann.add(tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization())

# Dense Layer
ann.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(128,activation='relu'))

# Normalize the data
ann.add(tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization())

# Flatten layer
ann.add(tf.keras.layers.Flatten())

# Dense Layer
ann.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(32,activation='relu'))

# Normalize the data
ann.add(tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization())

#Output layer
ann.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(num_classes,activation='softmax'))

#Configuring the model for training
ann.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

#D. Train a model using a basic CNN and share performance metrics on test data. [4 Marks]

#Initialize model
cnn2 = tf.keras.models.Sequential()

#Adding first convolutional layer
cnn2.add(tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(32, #Number of filters 
                               kernel_size=(3,3), #Size of the filter
                               activation='relu',
                               input_shape=(224,224,3)))

#Add MaxPooling layer 1
cnn2.add(tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)))

#Adding second convolutional layer
cnn2.add(tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(32, #Number of filters 
                               kernel_size=(3,3), #Size of the filter
                               activation='relu', padding='same'))

#Add MaxPooling layer 2
cnn2.add(tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)))

#Add dropout layer
cnn2.add(tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.25))

#Flatten the output
cnn2.add(tf.keras.layers.Flatten())

#Dense layer 1
cnn2.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='relu'))

#Add another dropout layer
cnn2.add(tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.25))

#Dense layer 2
cnn2.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='relu'))

#Add another dropout layer
cnn2.add(tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.25))

#Dense layer 3
cnn2.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='relu')) #, kernel_regularizer = tf.keras.regularizers.l2( l=0.01)

#Dense layer 4
cnn2.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='relu')) #, kernel_regularizer = tf.keras.regularizers.l2( l=0.01)

#Add anoter dropout layer
cnn2.add(tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.25))

#Output layer
cnn2.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(num_classes, activation='softmax'))

# Compile model
#adam_opt = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(lr=0.00001)
cnn2.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.RMSprop(lr=2e-4), 
              loss='categorical_crossentropy', 
              metrics=['accuracy'])

early_stopping = tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(monitor='val_acc', patience=5,verbose=1, mode='auto')
callback_list = [early_stopping]
